div.p:
The Papiſts doe ſo indeed, yet they deny their ſo doing becauſe they hold tranſubſtantiation, thereby Bellarmine would proue it to bee a ſlander, when we ſay they worſhip bread, and therfore need not ſay that intentionally and formally, but materially they doe it. Yet howſoeuer they doe, wee may vſe it neuertheleſſe freely,

and the geſture in vs is not liable to ſuſpition, becauſe we renounce their doctrine, and becauſe we haue no communion with them;
Rom. 16.16. as Saint Paul exhorted the Chriſtian gentiles to ſalute one another with an holy kiſſe, albeit the practiſe of kiſſing, not onely prophanely, but ſuperſtitiouſly alſo had bin abuſed, among them before; adhibita erant aſcula in deorum cultu;

                     2. Elect. cap. 6. as Lipſius ſhewes.
